# GuildCoreMatrix — Project Context

Senior WoW Addon Architect working on **GuildCoreMatrix**, a guild management
addon that organizes 10-man (Karazhan) and 25-man (Gruul / Magtheridon) cores
through a hybrid system based on Officer / Public Notes plus optional static
data sheets.

## Target client

- **WoW 2.5.5 — TBC Anniversary** running the modern Retail-based engine.
- TOC `## Interface: 20505`. Do NOT use Classic Era (`113xx`) or Retail (`110xxx`) APIs.
- Lua **5.1** semantics (no `goto continue`, no integer division `//`, no bitwise operators outside `bit` lib).

## Architecture rules

- Private namespace pattern at the top of every file:
  `local addonName, ns = ...`
- All modules attach to `ns` (e.g. `ns.Database`, `ns.Scanner`, `ns.UI`).
- UI uses `BackdropTemplate` mixin. **Never** use XML.
- Event handling goes through a single Event Dispatcher in `Core.lua`. Modules
  expose methods that the dispatcher calls; modules do not register their own
  global events unless strictly local (e.g. `PLAYER_LOGIN` for one-shot init).
- Data flows: Scanner → `ns.Cache` → UI refresh via `ns.UI:Refresh()`.

## Data schema (Officer / Public Notes)

Non-destructive regex parsing. Pattern: `[<TypeId>,<TypeId>...]` where
`Type` is one of:

- `k` → Karazhan 10m core
- `K` → Karazhan 25m core (uppercase)
- `G` → Gruul / Magtheridon 25m core

Each token may carry an optional role suffix: `:T` (Tank), `:H` (Healer), `:D` (DPS).

Example: `[K1:T,G2:H]` → Kara 10m core 1 as tank, Gruul core 2 as healer.

**Hard constraint**: Officer Notes have a **31-character limit**. Any feature
that writes back to notes must validate length before `GuildRosterSetOfficerNote`.

## Files of record

- `GuildCoreMatrix.toc` — load order, SavedVariables (`GCM_Settings`, `GCM_Cache`).
- `Core.lua` — Event Dispatcher only.
- `Modules/Locale.lua` — i18n registry + activation + callbacks. Loads first.
- `Locales/<code>.lua` — locale data (`enUS` is the required fallback).
- `Modules/Database.lua` — SavedVariables init (minimap pos, locale override).
- `Modules/Scanner.lua` — note parser, throttled (2s).
- `Modules/UI_Elements.lua` — class color / class icon / role icon / online dot / last-seen format helpers.
- `Modules/UI_Main.lua` — main frame (resizable, persisted) + slash commands (`/gcm [reset]`, `/gcmlang`).
- `Modules/UI_Member.lua` — member row mixin: tooltip, online dot, right-click menu (Invite / Whisper / Copy).
- `Modules/UI_FilterBar.lua` — search box + role/online toggles. Exposes `ns.UI.Filter` state and `:Matches(member)`.
- `Modules/UI_CoreList.lua` — card list with composition badge, warning border, collapse, "Invite all", and "Unassigned" section.
- `Modules/UI_Minimap.lua` — minimap toggle button.
- `Media/logo.tga` — addon icon.

See `i18n.mdc` for the localization contract and `wow-uiux-designer.mdc` for
visual conventions.

## Out of scope

- No external dependencies (no Ace3, no LibStub) unless explicitly requested.
- No XML files.
- No retail-only APIs (no `C_ChallengeMode`, no `C_MythicPlus`, etc.).
